41 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
42 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
43 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
44 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
45 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
46 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
47  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
48 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
49 #else
50 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
51 #endif
52 #endif
53 
54 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
55 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
56 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
57 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
58 #else
59 #error "unknown compiler"
60 #endif
61 
62 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
63 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
64 #else
65 #include <cstdio>
66 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
67  do { \
68  fputs(msg, stderr); \
69  DNNL_TRAP(); \
70  } while (0)
71 #endif

85 struct error : public std::exception {
86  dnnl_status_t status;
87  const char *message;
88 
93  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
94  : status(status), message(message) {}
95 
97  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
98 
104  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
105  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
106  }
107 };
108 
110 template <typename T>
111 struct handle_traits {};
112 
126 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
127 struct handle {
128 private:
129  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
130  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
131 
132 protected:
133  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
134  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
135 
136 public:
144  handle() = default;
145 
147  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
149  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
151  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
153  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
154 
160  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
161 
167  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
168  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
169  }
170 
178  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
179  T result = data_.get();
180  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
181  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
182  "attempt to use uninitialized object");
183  return result;
184  }
185 
190  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
191 
195  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
196 
204  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
205  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
206  }
207 
215  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
216 };

359 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
360  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
361  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
362  // returns a C type.

365  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),

591 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
592  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
593  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
594  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
595  } \
596 \
597  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
598  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
599  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
600  } \
601 \
602  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
603  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
604  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
605  } \
606 \
607  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
608  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
609  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
610  return lhs; \
611  } \
612 \
613  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
614  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
615  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
616  return lhs; \
617  } \
618 \
619  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
620  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
621  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
622  return lhs; \
623  } \
624 \
625  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
626  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
627  }
628 
629 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
630 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

933  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
934  dnnl_dim_t count;
935  int c_mask;
936  const float *c_scales;
937  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(
938  get(), &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
939  "could not get int output scales");
940  scales.resize(count);
941 
942  mask = c_mask;
943  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
944  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
945  }
946

966  (dnnl_dim_t)scales.size(), mask, &scales[0]),
967  "could not set int output scales");
968  }

1147  "could not create an engine");
1148  reset(engine);
1149  }
1150 
1151 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1152  engine(kind kind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
1159  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1160  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(
1161  &engine, convert_to_c(kind), device, context),
1162  "could not create an engine");
1163  reset(engine);
1164  }
1165 #endif
1166 
1172  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
1173  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1174  error::wrap_c_api(
1175  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1176  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
1177  "could not get engine from primitive_desc");
1178  reset(c_engine, true);
1179  }
1180 
1182  kind get_kind() const {
1183  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
1184  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
1185  "could not get the engine kind");
1186  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
1187  }
1188 
1189 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1190  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
1192  cl_context context = nullptr;
1193  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
1194  "could not get a context handle");
1195  return context;
1196  }
1197 
1199  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
1200  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
1201  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
1202  "could not get a device handle");
1203  return device;
1204  }
1205 #endif
1206 
1213  template <class primitive_desc>
1214  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
1215  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
1216  }
1217 
1218 private:
1219  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind kind) {
1220  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(kind);
1221  }
1222 
1223  template <class primitive_desc>
1224  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1225  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1226  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1227  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
1228  "could not get engine from primitive_desc");
1229  return engine(c_engine, true);
1230  }
1231 };

1249 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1250  using handle::handle;
1251 
1253  enum class flags : unsigned {
1256  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1258  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1260  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1262  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1263  };
1264 
1267  stream() = default;
1268 
1274  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags) {
1275  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1276  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&stream, engine.get(),
1277  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags)),
1278  "could not create a stream");
1279  reset(stream);
1280  }
1281 
1282 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1283  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1288  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1289  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1290  "could not create a stream");
1291  reset(stream);
1292  }
1293 
1295  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1296  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1297  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1298  "could not get OpenCL command queue");
1299  return queue;
1300  }
1301 #endif
1302 
1304  stream &wait() {
1305  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait a stream");
1306  return *this;
1307  }
1308 };

1719  gOdhwi4o = dnnl_gOdhwi4o,
1720  gOdhwi8o = dnnl_gOdhwi8o,
1721  gOIdhw16i16o = dnnl_gOIdhw16i16o,
1722  gOIdhw16o16i = dnnl_gOIdhw16o16i,
1723  gOidhw16o = dnnl_gOidhw16o,
1724  gOIdhw4i4o = dnnl_gOIdhw4i4o,
1725  gOIdhw4o4i = dnnl_gOIdhw4o4i,
1726  gOidhw4o = dnnl_gOidhw4o,
1727  gOIdhw8i16o2i = dnnl_gOIdhw8i16o2i,
1728  gOIdhw4i16o4i = dnnl_gOIdhw4i16o4i,
1729  gOIdhw8i8o = dnnl_gOIdhw8i8o,
1730  gOIdhw8o8i = dnnl_gOIdhw8o8i,
1731  };

1734  struct desc {
1735  friend struct memory;
1737  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1738 
1741  desc() : data() {}
1742 
1748  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1749  format_tag format_tag) {
1750  validate_dims(dims);
1751  error::wrap_c_api(
1752  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)dims.size(),
1753  dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
1754  convert_to_c(data_type), convert_to_c(format_tag)),
1755  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by tag");
1756  }
1757 
1763  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
1764  const memory::dims &strides) {
1765  validate_dims(dims);
1766  error::wrap_c_api(
1767  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data, (int)dims.size(),
1768  dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
1769  convert_to_c(data_type),
1770  strides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &strides[0]),
1771  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by strides");
1772  }
1773 
1777  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
1778 
1780  //
1784  desc submemory_desc(
1785  const memory::dims &dims, const memory::dims &offsets) const {
1786  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md;
1787  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1788  &sub_md, &data, &dims[0], &offsets[0]),
1789  "could not initialize a sub-memory");
1790  return desc(sub_md);
1791  }
1792 
1794  //
1797  desc reshape(const memory::dims &dims) const {
1798  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md;
1799  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(&out_md, &data,
1800  (int)dims.size(), &dims[0]),
1801  "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1802  return desc(out_md);
1803  }
1804 
1808  memory::dims dims() const {
1809  return memory::dims(data.dims, data.dims + data.ndims);
1810  }
1811 
1813  memory::data_type data_type() const {
1814  return static_cast<memory::data_type>(data.data_type);
1815  }
1816 
1820  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1821 
1823  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1824 
1829  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1830  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1831  }
1832 
1837  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1838  };
1839

1841  //

1843  // of a parameter.

1855  dnnl_memory_create(&result, &md.data, engine.get(), handle),
1856  "could not create a memory");
1857  reset(result);
1858  }
1859 
1866  memory(const desc &md, const engine &engine)
1867  : memory(md, engine, DNNL_MEMORY_ALLOCATE) {}

1874  return desc(*cdesc);

2009 struct primitive_desc_base : public handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> {

2020  const char *res;

2022  get(), dnnl_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
2023  "could not query implementation info string");

2028  memory::dim query_s64(query what) const {
2029  memory::dim res;
2030  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2031  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &res);
2032  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
2033  }
2034 
2046  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2047  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2048  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2049  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2050  query::exec_arg_md};
2051  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2052  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2053  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "invalid memory query");
2054 
2055  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2056  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2057  return memory::desc(*cdesc);
2058  }

2063  return query_md(query::src_md, idx);
2064  }

2069  return query_md(query::dst_md, idx);
2070  }

2075  return query_md(query::weights_md, idx);
2076  }

2081  return query_md(query::diff_src_md, idx);
2082  }
2083

2088  return query_md(query::diff_dst_md, idx);
2089  }
2090

2095  return query_md(query::diff_weights_md, idx);
2096  }

2161 
2163  dnnl::primitive::kind get_kind() const {
2164  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
2165  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
2166  dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
2167  "could not get primitive kind from the primitive descriptor");
2168  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);

2171 protected:
2172  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
2173  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
2174  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
2175  "could not clone primitive descriptor");
2176  reset(new_pd);
2177  }
2178 
2179  primitive_desc_base(
2180  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
2181  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
2182 
2183  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2184  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
2185  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
2186 
2193  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2194  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
2195  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
2196  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
2197  if (pd == nullptr) return;
2198 
2199  dnnl_status_t rc;
2200 
2201  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
2202  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
2203  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
2204 
2205  // Check that primitive kind matches
2206  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
2207  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2208  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
2209  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
2210  "could not get primitive kind from the primitive descriptor");
2211  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
2212  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2213  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
2214 
2215  // Check that propagation kind matches
2216  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
2217  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2218  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
2219 
2220  // Something went wrong
2221  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
2222  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2223  "could not get propagation kind "
2224  "from the primitive descriptor");
2225 
2226  // Everything is fine
2227  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
2228  || (rc == dnnl_success
2229  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
2230  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
2231  reset_with_clone(pd);
2232  return;
2233  }
2234 
2235  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
2236  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2237  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
2238  }
2239 
2240 protected:
2241  using base = primitive_desc_base;
2242 };
2243

2291  auto dst_md = dst.get_desc();
2292  error::wrap_c_api(
2293  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
2294  src.get_engine().get(), &dst_md.data,
2295  dst.get_engine().get(), attr.get()),
2296  "could not create a reorder primitive descriptor");
2297  reset(result);
2298  }

2313  }

2363 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
2364  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
2365  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
2366  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());

2368  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
2369  return c_mems;

2558 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
2559  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
2560 
2561  primitive_desc() = default;
2562 
2568  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
2569  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
2570  bool allow_empty = false)
2571  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
2572  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
2573  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
2574  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
2575  if (!allow_empty)
2576  error::wrap_c_api(
2577  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
2578  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
2579  fetch_impl();
2580  }
2581 
2588  bool next_impl() {
2589  dnnl_status_t status
2590  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
2591  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
2592  error::wrap_c_api(status, "primitive descriptor iterator next failed");
2593  fetch_impl();
2594  return true;
2595  }
2596 
2597 private:
2598  bool allow_empty_ = false;
2599  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
2600  void fetch_impl() {
2601  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
2602  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
2603  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
2604  : dnnl_runtime_error,
2605  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from the iterator");
2606  reset(pd);
2607  }
2608 };

5580  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(1); }
5581 
5583  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(2); }
5584 
5585 protected:
5586  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
5587 
5588  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
5589  //
5590  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
5591  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
5592  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
5593  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
5594  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
5595  //
5596  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
5597  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
5598  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
5599  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
5600  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
5601  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
5602  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
5603  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
5604  dnnl_status_t rc;
5605  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
5606  error::wrap_c_api(
5607  rc, "could not retrieve rnn_desc from a primitive descriptor");
5608 
5609  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
5610  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
5611  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
5612 
5613  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
5614  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
5615  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
5616  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
5617 
5618  if (!ok)
5619  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "rnn descriptor mismatch");
5620 
5621  reset_with_clone(pd);
5622  }
5623 };

7325 
7326 inline void primitive::execute(
7327  stream &stream, const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
7328  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
7329  c_args.reserve(args.size());
7330  for (const auto &a : args)
7331  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
7332 
7333  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
7334  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
7335  "could not execute a primitive");
7336 }
